    "body": "### Problem\n\nInserting a comment not on the current line, but rather on the line above or below is a very common task\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt would be useful to have default keymap for `gco` and `gcO` which would insert a comment on the line below or above, respectively\r\n\r\n## Examples\r\n\r\n### gco\r\n\r\nCursor: line 2\r\nMode: Normal\r\n```lua\r\n\r\nlocal random_number = 7\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter pressing `gco`\r\n\r\nCursor: line 3, at `<cursor>`\r\nMode: Insert\r\n```lua\r\n\r\nlocal random_number = 7\r\n-- <cursor>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### gcO\r\n\r\nCursor: line 1\r\nMode: Normal\r\n```lua\r\nlocal random_number = 7\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter pressing `gcO`\r\n\r\nCursor: line 1, at `<cursor>`\r\nMode: Insert\r\n```lua\r\n-- <cursor>\r\nlocal random_number = 7\r\n```",
